B.  Water Pollution  Management Specialist (international, 3 person-months) 

4.  The  water  pollution  management  specialist  should  have  a  post-graduate  degree  or 
equivalent and 15 or more years of experiences in the relevant fields. Demonstrated project-
related experience in the PRC is desirable. The consultant will undertake the following tasks: 

(i)  provide substantial inputs on the development and refining of a study framework 
and outlines of TA reports;  
(ii)  provide substantial inputs on the literature review of international practices and 
experiences in NPS pollution control, with focus on eco-compensation programs, 
water quality trading schemes, and best management practices; 
(iii)  provide  inputs  into  the  study  on  NPS  pollution  monitoring  and  measurement 
techniques, and their application in the Chao Lake basin and the PRC;  
(iv)  provide  guidance  and  inputs  on  the  design  and  implementation  of  household 
surveys for data collection; 
(v)  conduct a review of existing major NPS pollution management frameworks in the 
world, particularly those incorporating eco-compensation, water quality trading, 
and application of best management practices; 
(vi)  collaborate  with  the  national  consultants  on  developing  an  NPS  pollution 
management framework for the PRC with the team leader’s guidance; 
(vii)  participate in field trips to Chao Lake; 
(viii)  provide inputs on the TA reports, including the inception, interim, and final reports 
and their revised versions; and 
(ix)  conduct other related work assigned by the team leader. 

C.  Deputy  Team  Leader  and  Environmental  Policy  Specialist  (national, 10 person-
months) 

5.  The deputy team leader and environmental policy specialist should have a post-graduate 
degree or equivalent and 15 or more years of experience in the relevant fields. The consultant 
will assist the team leader in the coordination and supervision of the TA team. The consultant 
will be responsible for day-to-day liaison with the Ministry of Environmental Protection and other 
government  agencies  to  facilitate  TA  implementation.  The  consultant  will  undertake  the 
following tasks: 

(i)  assist the team leader in developing the detailed study framework in consultation 
with the executing agency, key stakeholders, and other experts;  
(ii)  assist the team leader in developing outlines of the inception, interim,  and final TA 
reports;

