F.  Agricultural Specialist (national, 5 person-months) 

8.  The agricultural specialist should have a post-graduate degree or equivalent and 10 or 
more years of experience in the relevant fields. The consultant will undertake the following tasks: 

(i)  provide substantial inputs on the development and refining of a study framework 
and outlines of TA reports;  
(ii)  conduct a literature review and analysis on the existing agricultural (crop and 
livestock farming) practices; 
(iii)  identify and assess the potential improvements in agricultural practices to reduce 
NPS pollution; 
(iv)  provide  inputs  on  the  study  of  NPS  pollution  monitoring  and  measurement 
techniques, and their application in Chao Lake and the PRC;  
(v)  provide inputs on the NPS pollution management framework regarding technical 
standards  or  requirements  for  agricultural  practices,  taking  Chao  Lake  as  a 
representative case;  
(vi)  participate in field trips to Chao Lake; 
(vii)  provide inputs on the TA reports, including the inception, interim, and final reports 
and their revised versions; and 
(viii)  conduct other related work assigned by the team leader. 

G.  Agricultural Policy Specialist (national, 6 person-months) 

9.  The agricultural policy specialist should have a post-graduate degree or equivalent and 
10 or more years of experience in the relevant fields. The consultant will undertake the following 
tasks: 

(i)  provide substantial inputs on the development and refining of a study framework 
and outlines of TA reports;  
(ii)  conduct a literature review and analysis on the existing agricultural (crop and 
livestock farming) policies and assess their impacts on farmers’ behavior and/or 
choices relating to NPS pollution (e.g., fertilizer purchase and use); 
(iii)  design and conduct household surveys, with the environmental economist, aiming 
to understand farmers’ behavior and choices related to NPS pollution, such as the 
purchase  and  application  of  fertilizer  and  pesticides,  and  waste  treatment  in 
livestock production;
